Christopher Graham
Co-Portfolio Manager

Nationwide Investor Destinations Funds, Nationwide Target Destination Funds
Mr. Graham is the Chief Investment Officer for Nationwide Funds and co-Portfolio Manager for Nationwide asset allocation strategies. He has more than 18 years of experience across asset management, investment banking, and wealth management. Since joining Nationwide in 2004, Mr. Graham’s duties have included managing several equity, fixed income and hedge fund allocations for Nationwide’s general account assets and internal business lines. Prior to Nationwide, Mr. Graham worked in investment banking and private equity at Borden Capital Management Partners and Salomon Brothers, Inc.  He also worked as a wealth management advisor at Salomon Smith Barney. Mr. Graham earned a bachelor’s degree in finance from Hampton University and a Master of Business Administration degree from The Wharton School of the University of Pennsylvania.
