Nationwide Fund Advisors Maintains Position in Lawson Products, Inc. (LAWS)

Posted by David Goldstein on Jul 21st, 2017 // No Comments 

Nationwide Fund Advisors continued to hold its position in shares of Lawson Products, Inc. (NASDAQ:LAWS) during the first quarter, according to its most recent disclosure with the Securities and Exchange Commission. The institutional investor owned 7,838 shares of the industrial products company’s stock at the end of the first quarter. Nationwide Fund Advisors owned approximately 0.09% of Lawson Products worth $176,000 as of its most recent filing with the SEC. 
Separately, Renaissance Technologies LLC increased its position in shares of Lawson Products by 33.7% in the fourth quarter. Renaissance Technologies LLC now owns 55,100 shares of the industrial products company’s stock worth $1,311,000 after buying an additional 13,884 shares during the period. Institutional investors and hedge funds own 65.68% of the company’s stock. 




Lawson Products, Inc. (NASDAQ LAWS) opened at 20.40 on Friday. Lawson Products, Inc. has a 1-year low of $15.28 and a 1-year high of $28.10. The firm has a 50-day moving average price of $21.47 and a 200 day moving average price of $22.86. The company’s market capitalization is $180.23 million. 


 Get Lawson Products Inc. alerts:



Lawson Products (NASDAQ:LAWS) last posted its quarterly earnings data on Thursday, April 20th. The industrial products company reported $0.09 EPS for the quarter, missing the Zacks’ consensus estimate of $0.10 by $0.01. The business had revenue of $74.62 million during the quarter, compared to analysts’ expectations of $72.22 million. Lawson Products had a negative net margin of 0.64% and a negative return on equity of 0.20%. During the same quarter last year, the firm earned $0.11 earnings per share. On average, equities analysts predict that Lawson Products, Inc. will post $0.39 EPS for the current year. 
COPYRIGHT VIOLATION WARNING: This piece of content was originally posted by BNB Daily and is the property of of BNB Daily. If you are accessing this piece of content on another site, it was illegally stolen and republished in violation of US & international copyright & trademark law. The legal version of this piece of content can be read at https://www.baseball-news-blog.com/2017/07/21/lawson-products-inc-laws-stake-maintained-by-nationwide-fund-advisors-updated.html. 
A number of brokerages recently issued reports on LAWS. Zacks Investment Research downgraded Lawson Products from a “hold” rating to a “sell” rating in a research note on Wednesday. ValuEngine upgraded Lawson Products from a “sell” rating to a “hold” rating in a research note on Friday, June 2nd. Finally, Barrington Research upgraded Lawson Products from a “market perform” rating to an “outperform” rating and set a $25.00 price target for the company in a research note on Friday, April 21st.
In other news, EVP Neil E. Jenkins sold 5,604 shares of Lawson Products stock in a transaction that occurred on Wednesday, June 14th. The stock was sold at an average price of $21.52, for a total value of $120,598.08. Following the sale, the executive vice president now directly owns 12,549 shares of the company’s stock, valued at $270,054.48. The sale was disclosed in a filing with the Securities & Exchange Commission, which is accessible through this hyperlink. Also, major shareholder Private Discipline Master Lkcm purchased 13,653 shares of the stock in a transaction dated Friday, May 26th. The stock was purchased at an average cost of $19.87 per share, for a total transaction of $271,285.11. The disclosure for this purchase can be found here. Insiders bought 15,767 shares of company stock valued at $311,557 over the last 90 days. Company insiders own 18.20% of the company’s stock. 
Lawson Products Company Profile
Lawson Products, Inc is a distributor of products and services the industrial, commercial, institutional and government maintenance, repair and operations (MRO) market. The Company’s product categories include fastening systems, fluid power, specialty chemicals, cutting tools and abrasives, electrical, aftermarket automotive supplies, safety, welding and metal repair, and other. 

 
