Nationwide Fund Advisors Has $219,000 Stake in Multi Packaging Solutions Intrntnl Ltd (NYSE:MPSX)


					Posted by Chloe McGuire on Jul 19th, 2017 // No Comments




Nationwide Fund Advisors reduced its position in shares of  Multi Packaging Solutions Intrntnl Ltd (NYSE:MPSX) by 6.2% during the first quarter, according to its most recent filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission. The firm owned 12,174 shares of the industrial products company’s stock after selling 799 shares during the period. Nationwide Fund Advisors’ holdings in Multi Packaging Solutions Intrntnl were worth $219,000 as of its most recent filing with the SEC. 
Several other hedge funds and other institutional investors also recently bought and sold shares of MPSX. Guggenheim Capital LLC increased its stake in  Multi Packaging Solutions Intrntnl by 6.1% in the fourth quarter. Guggenheim Capital LLC now owns 31,594 shares of the industrial products company’s stock worth $451,000 after buying an additional 1,813 shares during the last quarter.  State Street Corp increased its stake in  Multi Packaging Solutions Intrntnl by 9.1% in the fourth quarter. State Street Corp now owns 302,997 shares of the industrial products company’s stock valued at $4,320,000 after buying an additional 25,149 shares in the last quarter.  Candriam Luxembourg S.C.A. acquired a new stake in  Multi Packaging Solutions Intrntnl during the first quarter valued at about $4,849,000.  Finally, Chicago Capital Management LLC acquired a new stake in  Multi Packaging Solutions Intrntnl during the first quarter valued at about $623,000. 99.18% of the stock is currently owned by hedge funds and other institutional investors. 


 Get Multi Packaging Solutions Intrntnl Ltd alerts:



Multi Packaging Solutions Intrntnl Ltd (NYSE MPSX) traded up 0.06% on Wednesday, hitting $18.00. 152,007 shares of the stock were exchanged. Multi Packaging Solutions Intrntnl Ltd has a one year low of $11.00 and a one year high of $18.04. The company’s 50 day moving average price is $17.98 and its 200-day moving average price is $16.74. 





Multi Packaging Solutions Intrntnl (NYSE:MPSX) last announced its quarterly earnings results on Thursday, May 11th. The industrial products company reported $0.13 earnings per share for the quarter, missing the Thomson Reuters’ consensus estimate of $0.18 by $0.05. Multi Packaging Solutions Intrntnl had a net margin of 2.69% and a return on equity of 10.01%. The company had revenue of $382.60 million during the quarter, compared to analysts’ expectations of $395.21 million. During the same quarter last year, the firm posted $0.11 earnings per share. Multi Packaging Solutions Intrntnl’s revenue for the quarter was down 4.2% compared to the same quarter last year.  Analysts expect that  Multi Packaging Solutions Intrntnl Ltd will post $0.63 earnings per share for the current year. 
